Washington state will take over one that closed in January in Yakima, a major agricultural hub, and reopen it for coronavirus care.
Many more rural hospitals in Washington are tottering and hoping this crisis doesn’t overturn them.
“We see our rural hospitals as mission-critical,” Hochman says.
Some rural hospitals are grabbing for this lifeline.